icdar_EXTRACTED_train_df_dresnet50_20250.description:

        of the deepest feature map (the model returns multiple features map since it is a feature pyramid network)

icdar_train_df_patches_20250521_120324.c.description:
I am reducing the dimension of the patches at the level of words/characters
        For each unique index = (isEng,same_text) pair i select the m patches with more black pixels
        the final df has m*4 patches per writer, it adds the x,y,x1,y1 columns to extract the patch
        It also add an index column that is unique for each patch

icdar_train_df_words_sentences_20250522_.description:
I am extracting patches with words/sentences from the images
        For each unique index = (isEng,same_text) pair i split it in n_slices vertically
        then I select the best n_selected_lines lines per each slice and add (for each) a row
         to the dataframe with the x,y,x1,y1 vlues that define the patch
        It also add an index column that is unique for each patch
